{"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DiskInjector","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration","title":"DiskInjector","symbolKind":"enum","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit12DiskInjectorO","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DiskInjector","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"symbol"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Injects a user-data script into a VM’s guest disk as a macOS LaunchDaemon.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Type Properties","anchor":"Type-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector\/daemonLabel","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector\/guestScriptPath"],"generated":true},{"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector\/generateLaunchDaemonPlist()","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector\/generateMACAddress()","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector\/inject(script:into:)"],"generated":true}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/diskinjector"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DiskInjector","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before the VM boots, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiskInjector"},{"type":"text","text":" mounts the guest disk image on the host,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"writes a standard macOS LaunchDaemon plist and the user’s script to the data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"volume, then unmounts. When the VM boots, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launchd"},{"type":"text","text":" picks up the daemon and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"executes the script automatically — no SSH, no agent, no network required."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This uses Apple’s "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (ships with macOS) to attach APFS disk images"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and writes only to the data volume (never the Signed System Volume)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Usage","level":2,"text":"Usage"},{"code":["let scriptURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: \"\/path\/to\/setup.sh\")","let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","try DiskInjector.inject(script: scriptURL, into: bundle)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"How It Works","level":2,"anchor":"How-It-Works","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attaches the guest’s "},{"code":"disk.img","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" using "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" without mounting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(to discover the device node)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finds and mounts the APFS data volume from the attached disk."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes the user’s script to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/usr\/local\/bin\/spooktacular-user-data.sh"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the data volume."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes a LaunchDaemon plist to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/Library\/LaunchDaemons\/"},{"text":" that tells","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launchd"},{"type":"text","text":" to run the script at boot."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Detaches the disk image so the VM can boot cleanly.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Thread-Safety","level":2,"text":"Thread Safety"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are synchronous and use "},{"code":"Process","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to invoke "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Call from a background thread if needed to avoid blocking the main thread.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/DiskInjector":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DiskInjector","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Injects a user-data script into a VM’s guest disk as a macOS LaunchDaemon.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/diskinjector","kind":"symbol","title":"DiskInjector","role":"symbol"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create and manage macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon."}],"type":"topic","title":"SpooktacularKit","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","role":"collection"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/DiskInjector/generateLaunchDaemonPlist()":{"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keywo